{
  "text": "Our paper investigates the temporal upsampling problem. While previous approaches investigate in the framework of compressive sensing [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] , we formulate our work as fusing event streams with intensity images to obtain a temporally dense video. Compared to existing literature [CITATION_8] which integrates events per pixel across time, our differentiable model utilizes \"tanh\" functions as event activation units and imposes sparsity constraints on both spatial and temporal domain.",
  "correct_citation": {
